description: From Old French revendre, from Latin revēndere, from re- (“re-: again, back”) + vēndere (“to sell”). Equivalent to re- +‎ vend.

verbs.description: revend (third-person singular simple present revends, present participle revending, simple past and past participle revended)

entries.meaning: (archaic, transitive) Synonym of resell: to sell again.
(archaic, transitive) Synonym of return: to sell back to the original vendor.
